Another letter seeking financial support for the forthcoming royal wedding of Oluwo of Iwoland Oba Abdulrasheed Akanbi and a princess from Kano State has surfaced online. The fresh letter was signed by the Babalaje of Iwoland, Alhaji (Barr). Kudaisi Ismail Toyin. It emerged after the Oluwo debunked a viral letter seeking N20m support from Osun State Government on Friday for the wedding. Osun State Government noted the viral letter was a failed attempt by mischief makers to bring it and Governor Adegboyega Oyetola into “a collision course with the citizens”. - Advertisement - Kudaisi said the fresh letter is a surprise arrangement among chiefs to honour Oba Akanbi.   Segun Odegbami: I’m not a polygamist     Thugs attack Sunday Igboho’s residence, supporters in Ibadan     PHOTOS: Tinubu visits Awujale for royal blessings   He however said the monarch was not aware of the arrangement and letter. A copy of the letter sighted by The Nation, on February 7, 2022, was titled: ‘Notification of royal wedding of HRM, Oba, Dr. AbdulRasheed Adewale Akanbi Telu 1, and a princess of Ado Bayero dynasty’.  He said: “A few of the High Chiefs of Iwoland have consequently mandated me to constitute a committee to plan and see to the success of the wedding with a befitting royal ceremony. “At the inaugural meeting of the committee, we arrived at a modest tentative budget of N50 million to cover the traditional wedding Tambaya (introduction); Kai Kaya (engagement) and aqdu Nikkai. “The royal traditional wedding in Kano will be rounded up with a reception for the princess.” SPONSORED